Essar Of India to Spend as Much as $4 Billion on Zimbabwe Iron Ore Plant

-- B y   G o d f r e y   M a r a w a n y i k a
-- 
2011-08-03T10:58:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/essar-of-india-to-spend-as-much-as-4-billion-on-zimbabwe-iron-ore-plant.html
Essar Group, the Indian company that
bought the state-owned Zimbabwe Iron and Steel Co., plans to
spend between $2 billion and $4 billion on an iron ore plant in
the country, Commerce and Industry Minister  Welshman Ncube  said.  The plant will be situated in Mwanezi, south of the
capital, Harare, Ncube said at a ceremony today to mark the
handover of the company from the government.  Essar will also boost production at at an existing plant to
process 25 million metric tons of ore a year, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Godfrey Marawanyika in Johannesburg at 
